[Student "S"]
{NORTH has 19 points, but no 5-card Major suit. With two 4-card minor suits she should start 
with 1\D.

SOUTH has a poor hand, but with 7 points he must respond. His first priority is to show a Major suit 
so he responds 1\S.

NORTH now knows that \Ss will be trumps, so she revalues her hand to 21 points, enough for game. 
She bids 4\S.}

